# phase-multi-position.log — v1.82.0 multi-position + futsal vocabulary

## M1 — Schema audit + migration drafted

### Where position lives today

- **`PlayerLeagueMembership.position`** (`PlayerPosition?` enum: `GK | DF | MF | FW`). Per-league. The canonical source of truth.
- v1.65.4 explicitly DROPPED `Player.position` — Player is identity-only (name + lineId/userId + profilePictureUrl).
- `LeaguePositionFee.position` is `String` (not the enum) — fee resolver matches case-sensitively against `PLM.position`.
- Soccer enum codes used in code: `GK`, `DF`, `MF`, `FW`.
- `SquadList.tsx` / `MatchdayAvailability.tsx` ALSO recognise legacy strings `DF/MF`, `MF/FWD`, `FWD` (probably from an old Sheets-imported source that pre-dated the enum). They're not produced by any current write path, but the readers still color/sort them.

### League format fields

- `League.ballType BallType @default(SOCCER)` — enum `SOCCER | FUTSAL`.
- `League.playerFormat Int?` — 5/6/7/9/11. Independent.
- The position vocabulary in this PR keys off `ballType`, not `playerFormat`.

### Migration plan (additive, dual-write)

1. Add `positions String[] @default([])` to `PlayerLeagueMembership`.
2. Backfill on migration: `UPDATE "PlayerLeagueAssignment" SET positions = ARRAY[position::text] WHERE position IS NOT NULL`. Other rows stay `'{}'`.
3. KEEP legacy `position PlayerPosition?` for one cycle (cleanup PR after v1.82.0). Dual-write rule:
   - Always write `positions[]` (full array of String codes).
   - Also write `position` to the FIRST entry of the array IF that entry matches the soccer enum (`GK`/`DF`/`MF`/`FW`); otherwise write `null` (futsal-only codes can't fit the legacy enum).
4. Read fallback: prefer `positions[]`. If empty, fall back to `[position]` (or `[]` when null).

### Storage shape decision

- `String[]` (Postgres native array) — simpler than a join table for read paths and Prisma supports it. No FK / referential pressure since the vocabulary is a code list, not a row set.
- Stored as canonical UPPERCASE codes only (`GK`, `FIXO`, `ALA`, `PIVOT`, `DF`, `MF`, `FW`). Display labels in a separate map.

### Format vocabulary

- **Soccer** (`ballType = SOCCER`): `GK` (Goalkeeper), `DF` (Defender), `MF` (Midfielder), `FW` (Forward) — same as today.
- **Futsal** (`ballType = FUTSAL`): exactly four — `GK` (Goleiro), `FIXO` (Defender), `ALA` (Winger/Midfield), `PIVOT` (Striker).

## SPEC UPDATE (mid-implementation)

User updated soccer vocabulary from `GK/DF/MF/FW` to a 12-code positional set:
`GK, LB, CB, RB, LM, DM, CM, CAM, RM, LW, ST, RW`. Futsal stayed `GK/FIXO/ALA/PIVOT`.

Migration impact: existing `PlayerLeagueMembership.position` values (the
legacy 4-code enum) get mapped on backfill:
  - `GK` → `GK`
  - `DF` → `CB` (Center Back as the generalist default)
  - `MF` → `CM` (Center Midfielder)
  - `FW` → `ST` (Striker)

Bucket layer added (`getPositionBucket`) maps every code (legacy and new,
soccer and futsal) into the GK/DF/MF/FW band so colour/sort/formation
renderers stay simple and the legacy `PlayerLeagueMembership.position`
column keeps a sensible value via `legacyPositionFromArray`.

## M2 — Format vocabulary module + per-league wiring

- `src/lib/positions.ts` ships the canonical vocabulary, vocab/codes/labels lookup, the `normalizePositions()` validator, the `legacyPositionFromArray()` dual-write helper, and the `readPositions()` fallback.
- Soccer: GK / DF / MF / FW (unchanged).
- Futsal: GK (Goleiro) / FIXO (Defender) / ALA (Winger/Midfield) / PIVOT (Striker).
- Validation throws `Invalid position "FW" for FUTSAL …` on cross-format codes (verified by test).
- 24 unit tests in `tests/unit/positionsModule.test.ts` pin the vocabulary, validation, dedup, legacy fallback, and dual-write helper. All pass.

## M3 — UI + server-action wiring

### Server actions updated (positions[] in / dual-write out)
- `src/app/api/recruiting/actions.ts` — `applyToLeague`, `registerToLeague`. Validates against `league.ballType`, returns `{ ok: false, error }` on cross-format codes; dual-writes `positions[]` + bucketed legacy enum.
- `src/app/join/[code]/actions.ts` — `submitOnboarding`, `completeOnboardingWithId`. Same per-league validation + dual-write.
- `src/app/account/player/actions.ts` — `updatePlayerSelf`. Per-membership validation against each PLM's league.ballType so a user in mixed-format leagues isn't corrupted by a single submission.
- `src/app/admin/leagues/actions.ts` — `adminCreatePlayer`, `adminUpdatePlayerPosition`. Both pulled the league's ballType + validate. Removed the obsolete `normalizePosition` helper (legacy 4-code enum coercion).

### UI surfaces updated (chip multi-select)
- `src/components/PositionMultiSelect.tsx` — NEW. Shared chip picker; `variant: 'public' | 'admin'` for theming; canonical-vocab order on selection; per-chip aria-pressed + testid.
- `src/components/registration/RegistrationFields.tsx` — public registration form (recruit + onboarding).
- `src/app/recruit/[slug]/RegistrationForm.tsx` + `page.tsx` — fetches `league.ballType` and threads it through.
- `src/app/join/[code]/onboarding/OnboardingForm.tsx` + `page.tsx` — fetches `league.ballType` (via the invite's `league.ballType` select) and pre-fills `initialPositions[]`.
- `src/components/ApplyToLeagueModal.tsx` — multi-select.
- `src/components/RecruitingBanner.tsx` — passes `league.ballType` down.
- `src/components/Dashboard.tsx` + `src/app/page.tsx` + `src/app/id/[slug]/page.tsx` — added `ballType` to the `league` prop shape and per-league fetch.
- `src/app/account/player/AccountPlayerForm.tsx` + `page.tsx` — multi-select, picks ballType from the active membership.
- `src/components/admin/AddPlayerDialog.tsx` — admin-variant multi-select.
- `src/components/admin/PlayersTab.tsx` — `EditPlayerPanel` multi-select; `PlayerRow.positions[]` field; chip joining for compact display.
- `src/app/admin/leagues/[id]/players/page.tsx` — propagates `positions[]` into `PlayerRow`, threads `ballType` into `<PlayersTab>`.

### Read sites updated
- `src/lib/dbToPublicLeagueData.ts` — emits `Player.position` as `positions.join('/')` (preferred) with legacy single-string fallback.
- `src/components/SquadList.tsx` — colour + sort by role bucket (first code drives the band); preserves the joined-string display.
- `src/components/MatchdayAvailability.tsx` — `getPositionPillColor` + sort + formation grouping all bucket-driven; recognises both new 12-code and legacy single-letter shapes.
- `src/lib/admin-data.ts` — `getLinkablePlayersForLeague` returns `positions[]`; `mergedPendingApplications` carries `positions[]` from the PLM.
- `src/components/admin/LinkExistingPlayerDialog.tsx` — chip-joined display with legacy fallback.

